Tuần Châu is covered by pine forest, has an area of 2.2 km² and to the east and south are two man made beaches endowed with very white, fine sand.
Thien Cung Cave is 10,000 square meters with complicated interior structure, many floors, and high ceiling.
Yen Tu is famous all over the world for its beautiful landscapes, historical relics and hundreds of ancient pagodas and towers
Ha Long Bay is a UNESCO World Heritage Site, and a popular travel destination, in Quảng Ninh Province, Vietnam.
One of the outlying islands of the Ha Long Bay region and technically in BaiTuLong bay, has been sparsely inhabited for quite some time.
